{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.12",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 12",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 12 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:2",
      "text": "Are you then men alone, and shall wisdom die with you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:3",
      "text": "I also have a heart as well as you: for who is ignorant of these things, which you know?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:4",
      "text": "He that is mocked by his friends as I, shall call upon God and he will hear him: for the simplicity of the just man is laughed to scorn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:5",
      "text": "The lamp despised in the thoughts of the rich, is ready for the time appointed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:6",
      "text": "The tabernacles of robbers abound, and they provoke God boldly; whereas it is he that hath given all into their hands:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:7",
      "text": "But ask now the beasts, and they shall teach thee: and the birds of the air, and they shall tell thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:8",
      "text": "Speak to the earth, and it shall answer thee: and the fishes of the sea shall tell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:9",
      "text": "Who is ignorant that the hand of the Lord hath made all these things?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:10",
      "text": "In whose hand is the soul of every living thing, and the spirit of all flesh of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:11",
      "text": "Doth not the ear discern words, and the palate of him that eateth, the taste?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:12",
      "text": "In the ancient is wisdom, and in length of days prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:13",
      "text": "With him is wisdom and strength, he hath counsel and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:14",
      "text": "If he pull down, there is no man that can build up: if he shut up a man, there is none that can open.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:15",
      "text": "If he withhold the waters, all things shall be dried up: and if he send them out, they shall overturn the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:16",
      "text": "With him is strength and wisdom: he knoweth both the deceivers, and him that is deceived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:17",
      "text": "He bringeth counsellors to a foolish end, and judges to insensibility.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:18",
      "text": "He looseth the belt of kings, and girdeth their loins with a cord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:19",
      "text": "He leadeth away priests without glory, and overthroweth nobles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:20",
      "text": "He changeth the speech of the true speakers, and taketh away the doctrine of the aged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:21",
      "text": "He poureth contempt upon princes, and relieveth them that were oppressed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:22",
      "text": "He discovereth deep things out of darkness, and bringeth up to light the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:23",
      "text": "He multiplieth nations, and destroyeth them, and restoreth them again after they were overthrown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:24",
      "text": "He changeth the heart of the princes of the people of the earth, and deceiveth them that they walk in vain where there is no way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.12.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:25",
      "text": "They shall grope as in the dark, and not in the light, and he shall make them stagger like men that are drunk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
